addendum to Majordomo2 "configset default_flags" File - updated 24 Feb 99

NOTE: These supply defaults for new subscribers. Once subscribed, the
user can change their own settings on a per-list per-subscriber basis.
See "help set" for more information, including digest and nomail settings.

These flags correspond to these "set" commands:
          A  - set listname ackall          EmailAddress
          a  - set listname ackimportant    EmailAddress
(no a, no A) - set listname noack           EmailAddress
          C  - set listname eliminatecc     EmailAddress
      (no C) - set listname noeliminatecc   EmailAddress
          H  - set listname hideall         EmailAddress
          h  - set listname hideaddress     EmailAddress
(no h, no H) - set listname nohide          EmailAddress
          P  - set listname prefix          EmailAddress
      (no P) - set listname noprefix        EmailAddress
          R  - set listname replyto         EmailAddress
      (no R) - set listname noreplyto       EmailAddress
          S  - set listname selfcopy        EmailAddress
      (no S) - set listname noselfcopy      EmailAddress


==> see also: set  (for how a user can set these options after subscribing)
==> see also: configset ack_denials_always  (overrides "noack" for denied posts)
==> see also: configset allowed_flags (restricts subscribers ability to use set)


